The paper deals with real-time path planning for autonomous driving, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a fully convolutional neural network (FCN) to predict path regions, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of machine learning and neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application of the method in autonomous driving systems suggests the paper could also be categorized under control systems (cs.SY).
